content.detailedDescription:
it was on a clear day last week, around the 25th of march. i was standing next to my house, looking up at the sky, observing the chemtrails which i do often. it wasn't a heavy chemtrail day, just a couple of xes and lines that were spreading out. suddenly i noticed something moving quickly past the trails. my eyes focused on what i first thought was a flock of birds in the far distance. it looked like bunch of dots in a formation. i'm wasn't sure how many, maybe ten or twelve, because this formation of dots was moving very fast. when i noticed them, they were directly in front of me, but within 2 to 3 seconds they had traveled across the sky to my left until they vanished in the distance.
     i stood there a few minutes thinking about what i just saw, wondering what it could have been. if it wasn't for the speed, it could have been a flock of birds so far away that they looked like dots. then i thought it could have been a group of insects that were quite close to me streaking by and staying in a perfect formation. maybe a squadron of jet fighters? but there was no noise made by this ufo. i thought it couldn't have been any of these things because it was just moving to fast.    
     i didn't think much more about my sighting until last night when i saw the photo of the london sighting. it appears to be the same kind of formation only closer to the viewer. could it be that there's a ufo squadron speeding around globe? i think it's a possibility.
content.summary: Looked like the london sighting, but streaked across the sky at incredible speed.

content.detailedDescription: Everything started on the night of the 15th of october,2005 at around 10:30 pm,i was watching the sky (as is my usual habit)when suddenly,in a west to south direction,at a 60 degree angle,i saw a fireball moving at slow speed,the fireball would stop for a few seconds at a time so that it took a few minutes (2 or 3) to cross the sky in from of me,at about 11:45 pm i decided to go to bed.Them at about 1:30 am, i woke up to go to the bathroon and while in the bathroon i looked up through the skylight and realized that the fireball was clearly visible on the left hand side of the skylight.I observed the fire ball for about 5 minutes.It was standing still in the sky.By then it was the morning of the 16th of october 2005.I was still observing the fireball closely when i thought about looking for something with which to tape it,i found a camera and decid to take a photograph,i lowered the camera to observe the fireball on the photograph and saw that it was dark,the i decided to take a second photograph,and when i took it,i lowered the camera again to observe the photograph.Upon observing it,ifound the great surprise and felt much fear.So much that i decided to shut off the camera and run to bed.The next day,in the clear of morning,i decided to ckeck out the camera to make sure that what i saw was the same as what i saw through screen.Yes what i saw was evidenced in the picture i took.It was the clear and distinct picture of what seemed like proyected e.T. faces.I dont know how they got there,close enough to peer through the sky-light.I dont know if the proyection of the faces come from the fireball that was above me,over the the skylight.Or what. the truth is,that i dont know what that was.
content.summary: Fireball and e.T. picture.

content.detailedDescription: This all happened in the north east of england in the summer of 1976/77. i was about 8 or 9years old at the time, i do remember it was a monday night. i had gone to bed at about 9.00pm. it was one of those nights where the summer night sky was a light brown colour, you could see objects on ground a couple of houses away. my bedroom was on the upper floor at the rear of the house in the little town called hartburn in north yorkshire. i had gone to sleep but soon woke with a strange feeling over me, it was hard to explain, i just felt like i needed to look out of my window. my bed was near the window so i just sat up and peered out of the corner of the curtains, the sky was very clear, as i looked to the right out of the window i saw an object floating over an oak tree in the rear of a neighbours house about 4 doors down. it was as round as the canopy of the tree. about 1/2 as deep as the canopy of the tree. just under the rim of the disk seemed to have a dim orange glow that pulsated. i watched it for what seemed like 5 or 10 minutes then i suddenly got a very spooky feeling that i should not be watching it, i then closed over the curtains, that was when i started hearing strange noises in the air, all i remember is that it felt like wolves howling way off in the distance. not what you would hear i the north of england.I ended up huddled under the covers with them pulled over my head. after a while (not sure how long) the whole feeling and the noises just stopped. after a few minutes i got the guts to look out the window again. the object was gone. so i had a good look around and noticed it was way off in the distance now and then it just seem to streak up steeply and it was gone. it was then that i felt that all was normal again, it was like the air was all tense and then just all gone and back to normal. i told mum and dad the next day but they just put down to my imagination. but i am not 40 years old and i will not forget it at all.
content.summary: Ufo sighting as a child with strange noises that followed in the house.

content.detailedDescription: I was riding my atv late with a friend. we stopped to take a break in a nursery clearing in painesville ohio. it was a very clear night and could clearly see the stars, the half moon was really bright. over the tree line you could clearly see the lights of painesville city.  my friend and i were talking, not even looking toward the sky. i caught a movement out of the corner of my eye and turned to see what it was and saw a sphere of light make a circle air manuver that had to cover an imposssible distance in just over a second. i originally thought it was a flashlight for a split second because i saw light movement and thought someone was coming. i started watching the light and noticed that it had red and blue flashing twinkling lights all around it. it seemed to hover in the same place for a while after doing the circle manuver and then started to slowly move in sharp angles left to right, up and down, stopping abruptly and then going in the opposite direction than it originally came. it would also make slight curving turns, stopping abruptly. it was clearly over the space of painesville city. the direction in the sky was north, possibly toward the lake. the field that we were parked in was very wide open and you could see for miles. the main abundance of light from the ground was coming from painesville city. and this object was high in the sky over the city and was clearly not a city light, tower, plane etc..It was entirely too high in the sky for anything like that..I watched this thing for close to a half hour make darting movements in the same part of the sky. i would have never noticed the object if it would have not made the circle movement out of the corner of my eye. if you were to just glance at it for a second you would probably mistake it for a plane becasue of the red and blue flashing lights but this thing clearly made airial movements like i have never seen befor, covering vast distances in the sky and stopping abruptly.I felt like i was witnessing something unworldly and i seemed to be drawn to it and could not look away..After a half hour or so, we headed back to the trucks because it was almost midnight. this has really sparked my interest and i plan on going back with a camera just for the chance it would be back. i know what i saw and would take a lie detector test to prove it.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription:
I have been monitoring the skys over pheonix arizona since early march 2009 using the adeq (arizona department of air quality) web cams from my home in the san francisco bay area. i became interested in doing this as a result of seeing the film the pheonix lights a few months ago. i also stumbled on a web site www.Webcamufo.Com that allows you to download zoomable high resolution pictures from the phoenix web cams. in just a few short days of watching these cams starting in the early evening hours, i've been able to capture more than two dozen unusual objects in the air over phoenix. i have no idea what they are but i am cureous to find out. i have attached three of the more interesting ones for all to see. i saved the original high resolution 5.6mb images that i used to crop these three from as well as the dozens of others i have.

if anyone would like more information or you would like me to supply you with the original high res pictures please feel free to contact me through the folks at mufon.

content.detailedDescription: "j" was water superintendent for tabor, iowa. he was driving in his truck 10/17/1988 to the tabor wells which are 4 mi east of tabor. when he got there he noticed nothing. it was 7:10 am when he got back in his truck, engine off. he said he heard a roar for a few seconds and the sound was so loud it was like it was on top of him. he got out and looked up for a jet and noticed an object in the field to the se. he got back in his truck and watched the object. he said the roar caused no dust. it was just getting light and there were no stars out. the object was cross-shaped, 500-600 feet high and about 700-800 feet away. he could see it from underneath and said it was silver. he looked for lights but could see none. he was in his pickup with the window down and watched for 10-15 minutes trying to figure out what it was. he said a pencil erasure tip at arm's length would cover the object. he said an arm or point came out 4 or 5 times and when it did there was an orange glow (circular) around the object. there was no sound after the intial roar. he saw his son-in-law coming down the road and thought "i want him to see this". he was in a tractor with a cab. the object kept the same perspective to the witness as it moved away and seemed to get smaller and smaller. it shrank or moved out of sight in about 30 seconds, before the son-in-law got to the witness. the roar was earlier when the witness first saw the object. the son-in-law told the witness he saw or heard nothing. either before or after (he was not sure) his son-in-law got to him, he went back west to the top of a hill to see if he could again see the object. when he went back to the maintenance shop in town, tabor, the mayor and others were there. he told the mayor what he saw. the mayor said "don't tell anybody. they won't believe you". he only told a few people. i asked if there might be any traces in the field and he said it had been disked several times. i did not go to the area with the witness, but i had a good description. it was rainy and foggy when i was there. i learned about this report from jean sorenson who is a friend of jack's. i sent in a report earlier of a sighting she had. jack's wife wrote it down in her diary so we knew the date. also his son-in-law said the night before ufo coverup live was on tv. "j" said he didn't see the show. original report sent to ray boeche, mufon, 2/27/1989.
content.summary: Silver cross-shaped object. noticed after roaring sound. an arm extended 4-5 times with orange glow. object appeared to shrink and disappear. 1 witness. 10-15 min. time am.

content.detailedDescription: I was on my way back from a fun trip to las vegas, nevada, at the approx. times i listed.  the jet was headed back to texas.  we had just taken off and had only been in flight for about 5 minutes.  i was sitting next to the window on the side where you cold actually see the grand canyon and hoover dam below, as i had seen them on the way in, sitting on the same side in the jet, by the window. ---thoughts of "area 51" went through my head for a few seconds as we were in beginning flight.....Then i turned away from the window for about 1-2 minutes, then i began looking down to see if i could see hoover dam again....Then my eyes went upwards parallel to the clouds and jet's wing...And there it was!---parallel to our jet and about 50-100 yards away was this silver,metallic flying disc/saucer!---it was just hovering there in place for about 5-10 seconds as if it were observing our jet!---so i turned to the person next to me,(whom i did not know, and nudged her with my hand, and told her to look out the window so that she would also see the saucer, but by the time we both looked out the window----it was gone)!------i just had to report this, even if it's about 11yrs. later because...I know what i saw, and isn't it amazing that i had heard there was stuff like that going on at "area51" with ufo's and aliens, and then i end up seeing one near the vicinity of 'area 51?!?'---so there must be something to this 'area 51' after all!
content.summary: Silver shaped saucer/disc.

content.detailedDescription:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
in the spring of 1979 i was driving with a friend in virginia. we were not too far from skyline drive and west virginia going towards washington, d.C. it was very early in the morning and still very dark. i saw a bright orange sphere hovering over the tree tops. i slowed down then stopped the car behind two other cars that had pulled over to the side of the road. a couple people stood outside their cars looking up at the sphere, but i was too afraid to get out of my car and just rolled down the window about half way. the sphere was bright, silent and i didn't notice any indication of turbulence of the atmosphere around it. after a couple minutes it ascended straight up out of site at an incredible speed. in what seemed like 1 - 2 seconds it was out of the atmosphere out of site. it left no trail of emissions behind it. i did not approach the other witnesses and drove away frightened. my friend slept through the entire event even though i tried to get her to wake up telling her that i thought i was watching a ufo. i have always considered that there may have been an explanation other than ufo and remain open to suggestions. i have often wondered what the other witnesses thought of this siting. if only i had been brave enough to venture over to them. it was prudent to not approach them because we were two young women traveling through a pretty isolated area. i have told my family and friends that i believe i may or may not have seen a ufo. any similar sitings out there? all explanations welcome.
content.summary: Bright orange self-illuminated sphere.

content.detailedDescription:
As soon as we witnessed this ufo, i called my husband who is a mufon state section director as well as a field investigator & was in contact with him throughout the entire event to give him a full description of what was going on, but unfortunately we could not get a good picture at all.

1.  we just left the oxford valley mall in langhorne, pa and were in the car coming home.

2.  i saw something flying in the sky and it appeared to be sparkling.

3.  i had absolutely no idea what it was-i thought it was a little too exotic to be an airplane. i was in the front passenger seat and asked my friend's daughter- who was sitting in the rear drivers seat- to look at the object flying in the sky. when she moved over to my side of the car to look out the window- she freaked out.

4. at first it appeared to be a u shape- but after i got my friend's daughter to look at it with me it appeared to be oval shaped. it was so bright and appeared to be glittering with colors not associated with airplanes. yes, there were red, green and white lights- but also lime green, pink, magenta, purple, orange and yellow- with a gold background. it was shimmering and glittery- (it reminded me of holding a diamond ring under a bright light with all the facets reflecting color.) the colors were more heavily concentrated in the front, but were all over the oval shape. it appeared to be 3 inches long and 1 1/2 inches high out the window, where i didn't need to really extend my neck to look up at it. it remained in sight the whole time we drove and was anywhere from 12 to 18 inches behind my line of sight.

5&6 i got this tingling sensation up and down my right arm but was not afraid. it was actually the most beautiful thing i have ever seen. i couldn't take my eyes off it. i kept laughing while my friend's daughter was freaking out. i called my husband to tell him about what we saw and he told me to get a picture of it. my friend sped up and pulled into a vacant lot. as we jumped out of the minivan, the object approached and turned right. it changed into a straight line. as we attempted to capture it on film, it dissapeared.
content.summary: I was in a car with 2 friends leaving the oxford valley mall & i saw a bedazzled ufo.

content.detailedDescription:
At 8:45 pm on tuesday night, march 31, 2009, i was out in my driveway cleaning some mud off of my shoes when i took a minute to admire the stars on a clear night. my eyes focused upon a stationary object off to my northeast at what my father, who i asked to come out to see the object, estimated to be at about 3,000 feet up in altitude. we looked at it through two different sets of binoculars. my description of the object is of the lights associated with it, as it was too dark and the lights too bright to be able to make out a shape. as for colors, i saw greens, reds, and light yellows. the lights pulsed in a rapid series of movements, so much so, that they actually made me a bit dizzy after a couple of minutes of focusing upon them with the binoculars. at times, the lights seemed to diminish in brightness and intensity of movement, but would shortly resume their previous brightness and frenetic movement. the lights moved frenetically, but the object that they emanated from stayed perfectly still. the object made no sound that was observable to me or to my father. 

as i watched it, i remarked to my father that this was officially my first sighting of a ufo. after about 30 minutes of watching the object, it either started to move off slowly towards the northeast, or the lights it emitted were reduced in intensity and movement, i couldn't tell which. about five minutes after that, i went back into the house, even though the object was still visible, in the diminished state i just described.
content.summary: Witnessed object est. 3k feet up in clear night sky: stationary multiple colored lights moving rapidly.

content.detailedDescription: Okay, i looked outside and noticed it was all starry and clear, so i decided to set my telescope up in my room. after it was set up, i looked to see where if there any planets and i noticed a weird looking star. my eyesight is not that good even with my contacts in so i assumed my eyes were distorting it slightly. i did notice that everything else was really clear compared to most nights. anyways, this star looked slightly wider at the sides and did appear to twinkle just a little too much. (by the way this star was not moving at all or did not appear to be moving.) i decided i would point my telescope at this star, but i had to move my telescope to the other side of my room. so i did that and looked again and it was still there. then, i went to pick my lens up and slide it into place (took no more then 5 seconds). when i looked up again it was gone. there were no clouds and every other star looked just as clear. it was near trees but the direction of the earths orbit would naturally make it rise (in the east) so i figured it wasn���t just a star moving across the sky. this is the first ufo i have ever seen. there may be an explanation for it but i can���t explain it, so i am classifying it and an unidentified flying object.
content.summary: It just disappeared!

content.detailedDescription: 6 white lights appeared in the west sky on route 16 heading south. time was 20:55 hours. they moved quickly, making no noise, heading to the east sky of route 16 heading south. total time lapse 22 seconds. i was driving home from springville after just going grocery shopping at wal-mart. i was driving on route 16 heading south to machias when i saw 6 white lights in the western sky. they were at first formulated in a parallelogram shape pattern but then started to make a straight line. these lights continued over my vehicle, making no noise, into the eastern sky. i continued to watch until they disappeared. the time i noted was 20:55 (8:55pm) on my wristwatch then when they disappeared it was 20:55:22 (8:55:22pm). i could account for no sound because i had my window rolled down and it was a clear night as well.
content.summary: 6 unidentified lights in parallelogram pattern.

content.detailedDescription:
While i was out on my deck smoking a cigeratte, i was looking at the moon and noticed how bright it was.  it looked like the moon was moving which we all know it doesn't move, we do and not enough for me to notice.  i ran in and got my son's digital camera (which i have never used).  i came out and took about 5 pictures of the moon.  as i was taking the pictures, i noticed through the camera that the color of the moon had changed to red like a fiery sunset and then a blue color.  then i decided to drive to get a different view and went to gary lane and across the street is a dead end road, i rode to the end and the moon was bright but you could clearly see there was nothing in front of it as i had just seen.  i went home.

the next day, i asked my son to downloaded the pictures and asked him what he saw.  he stated that there was red in one picture and he thought there was blue in another and wanted to know what i had been looking at.  i explained and after reviewing them, we decided to enhance the pics to see what we could see and there was something there.  what i don't know.  the direction the moon was in that night was east of exeter, nh and the next town is either hampton or seabrook.  (seabrook nh has a nuclear power plant).

the actual thing i saw was triangle looking once it moved away from the moon.  there were 3 blue lights on it and it was at an angle.

yes, i believe it was a ufo and it moved away and out of the sky itself.


the camera timestamp is incorrect, the time had just changed on march 8th to 1 hour ahead and we did not adjust the camera.
content.summary: Looked like something was overlapping the moon.

content.detailedDescription:
All   this is in the sighting report sent in by the witness
so is her address and all the other invofrmation below.

my conclusion is is below in the final box

I just dropped off a friend at his house at 22:15. it was a nice night out, so i took the long way home. i was coming to an an intersection. i remember seeing the stop sign, but don't remember coming to it, or stopping. the next thing i know i am starting my car, and i am turing to wave good bye to my friend. i realized i wasn't at his house, but near a corn field... parked. i began to panic and looked down at my feet and my shoes were all muddy. i got out of my car caught my breath and regained myself. i look around and just could comprehend what just happened. i got back in and looked at the clock. i lost an hour. i look at my watch (this is the most troubling thing) it is a dual analog and digital watch. the didital portion was an hour off than the analog. i drove home with a very funy feeling. but i felt fine. not tired, sore, sick. i felt great! other than my sense of panic of what happeded. i feared that i had some sort of seizure, or something. 

the next morning i contacted my brother. he is very much into the ufo phenomena, and has had a few experiences in his life, but more so he just has done a lot of research in this area of study. he told me i should make contact with you guys and share with you my story.

later today i finally decided to drive out where i found myself. it was very strange to be there again. as i drove around the field (a place i have never been) it seemed all too familiar to me. like i had been there, and deep down inside a feeling of comfort and yet complete terror. i have tried to look at this logically and the only conclusion i can come up with is something happened, that had altered time (the watch and clock). beyond that i have no logical explanation.

in short, it was like being put to sleep for surgery. one minute your looking up at the lights and doctors, and the next you are in recovery. the differance was, i was sleepy, or groggy. i was perfectly awake, and tring to start the car just as if i turned off to drop him off, and i was starting it again. but only an hour later 2 miles away.

i know this sounds crazy! it does to me right now, but i just can't explain what happened.
content.summary: Didn't see anything but lost an hour.
